🚀 Project Name: Campus-Flow
The Mission: "Eliminate canteen queues by allowing students to pre-order, track, and collect meals using digital tokens."
🛠 Tech Stack (The Modern Industry Standard)
Frontend: Next.js 15 (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui.
Backend: Next.js Server Actions (Node.js environment).
Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL).
Real-time Logic: Supabase Realtime (WebSockets).
Authentication: Supabase Auth (Restricted to @college.edu emails).
Payments (Optional/Demo): Razorpay Test Mode.
📊 Phase 1: Database Schema (The Backend Foundation)
Sabse pehle ye 4 tables design karni hain Supabase mein:
Profiles: id, full_name, email, role (STUDENT/STAFF).
Menu_Items: id, name, price, category, is_available (Boolean), image_url.
Orders: id, user_id, total_price, status (PENDING, PREPARING, READY, COLLECTED), token_number, created_at.
Order_Items: id, order_id, menu_item_id, quantity.
⚙️ Phase 2: Core Backend Logic (Your Practice Area)
Ye 3 features aapke backend ko "Senior Level" banayenge:
1. The "Transaction-Safe" Ordering
Jab bacha "Order" dabaye, toh backend ko ye ensure karna hai:
Student ke paas sufficient balance hai? (Agar wallet system hai).
Kya item sach mein available hai?
Order aur Order_Items dono tables mein ek saath entry honi chahiye (Database Transaction).
2. Real-time Status Sync (WebSockets)
Bacha order karke baith gaya. Canteen wala button dabaye "Ready":
Backend status update karega READY.
Supabase Realtime bache ki screen par bina refresh kiye status change kar dega.
Backend Practice: Real-time data subscription seekhoge.
3. Secure Token Verification
Khana collect karte waqt bacha ek QR code ya Token dikhayega.
Staff scan karega/verify karega.
Backend status ko COLLECTED kar dega aur wo order history mein chala jayega.
📱 Phase 3: The User Experience (Screens)
Student Side:
Home: Categories (Chai, Maggi, Lunch).
Cart: Items add karo aur "Place Order" dabao.
Order Tracking: Ek simple visual timeline (Order Placed -> Preparing -> Ready).
Canteen Side (The System):
Active Orders Board: Bade-bade cards jisme likha ho "Token #45 - 2 Samosa".
Status Toggles: Staff bas ek click se status change karega.
Menu Management: Ek button se "Chai" ko "Sold Out" mark kar dena.
🏁 Phase 4: Roadmap (3 Weeks)
Week 1: Setup Next.js + Supabase. Menu items database mein daalo aur unhe frontend par dikhao. (CRUD Operation).
Week 2: Cart functionality aur Order placing logic. (Database Transactions).
Week 3: Canteen Staff Dashboard aur Real-time status updates. (WebSockets/Realtime).
